          <h1 class="balance no-widow">This Site: safe architecture, measurable proof</h1>
          <p data-site-thissite-intro>This page explains how the platform is designed, protected, and operated without exposing secrets, identifiers, or implementation details that would increase attack surface.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="this-site-proof-grid" data-site-thissite-proof-grid>
          <article class="this-site-proof-card">
            <h2>What this proves</h2>
            <p>Production-minded architecture can remain public and understandable while still enforcing strict identity, boundary, and logging controls.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="this-site-proof-card">
            <h2>What stays private</h2>
            <p>No account IDs, no bucket names, no database UUIDs, no secret names/values, and no policy bypass mechanics are documented here.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
