    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>High-level architecture</h2>
        <p>Public content is served by Pages, while data and admin mutations pass through the Worker API into D1 and R2. Bot checks and identity checks are applied before privileged operations.</p>
        <figure>
          <img src="/assets/this-site-architecture.svg" alt="High-level diagram: Pages frontend to Worker API with D1 and R2 data services, protected admin path via Cloudflare Access." loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <figcaption class="meta-line">Topology only: Pages → Worker → D1 + R2, with public and protected admin paths.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>Identity &amp; access</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare Access</strong> gates admin surfaces before application logic is reached.</li>
          <li><strong>RBAC</strong> is enforced in the Worker for <strong>admin</strong> and <strong>reviewer</strong> roles.</li>
          <li><strong>Audit events</strong> capture role, action class, and outcome for each write-path operation.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>Security controls</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Turnstile</strong> on public write paths to reduce automated abuse.</li>
          <li><strong>Rate limiting</strong> at edge/API boundaries to contain burst misuse.</li>
          <li><strong>Validation + sanitization</strong> for inbound payloads and persisted records.</li>
          <li><strong>Audit log</strong> for mutation traceability and post-incident reconstruction.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>Operations model</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Migrations:</strong> schema changes are versioned and applied in controlled order.</li>
          <li><strong>Deploy workflow:</strong> CI builds static assets and deploys Worker + Pages with repeatable steps.</li>
          <li><strong>Rollback / compensation:</strong> immutable frontend rollback plus compensating data actions when direct reversal is unsafe.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <h2>Cost control &amp; storage hygiene</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Media delete operations remove unused assets to reduce retained storage.</li>
          <li>Periodic hygiene checks identify orphaned files and stale references.</li>
          <li>Operational reviews prioritize predictable egress/storage spend over uncontrolled growth.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
